    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <head>No. 297.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Everett</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-10-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 20,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 268.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of your dispatch,
                        No. 254, of the 27th ultimo, in relation to the invitation to the von
                        Steuben family to attend the Yorktown centennial celebration, I have to
                        inform you that your action in securing passage on the Herder, at the
                        expense of this government, for the seven officers who accepted the
                        invitation in question, is fully approved by this Department.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                        Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
